The paper discusses the documentation of machine learning software, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG) domains. The authors also mention the use of natural language processing techniques for summarization and explanation, which relates to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper focuses on understanding the types and triggers of problems in documentation, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
